      "writtenOn": "2017-09-26T13:35:55Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Ok, just looked at crbug.com/765590 and I see the problem in the video. (I\u0027m on an old version of Chrome so I didn\u0027t see the problem by just opening the image in Chrome.)\n\nIt\u0027s interesting that this image specified a transparent index that is not valid, and then used it. (As opposed to say, not specifying a transparent index and then arbitrarily using indices between 64 and 255 any time it wanted to have transparency.)\n\nA more conservative fix here would just be\n\n  return transparentPixel \u003e\u003d 0 \u0026\u0026 transparentPixel \u003c maxColors;\n\nThat would fix this particular image, with less false positives (e.g. marking frames without transparent pixels as having alpha even though they have no transparentPixel, just because they have small color maps). It would still leave other (more?) broken images broken.\n\nThe other side of the fix might be to fix broken encoders out there in the world? Wouldn\u0027t correct existing images, though.",
